00:01:01,270 --> 00:01:02,690
but orthogonal ones.

15
00:01:02,690 --> 00:01:04,230
So what does that mean?

16
00:01:04,230 --> 00:01:08,600
That means that every q is
orthogonal to every other q.

17
00:01:08,600 --> 00:01:13,880
It's a natural idea,
to have a basis that's

18
00:01:13,880 --> 00:01:17,060
headed off at
ninety-degree angles,

19
00:01:17,060 --> 00:01:19,120
the inner products are all zero.

20
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:26,260
Of course if q is -- certainly
